<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="127" type="pollen">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Pollen.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="127">
pantocolpate, radially symmetrical, isopolar with circular contour in polar view. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Shape</emphasis>
: oblate-spheroidal (P/E=0.99). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Apertures</emphasis>
: 12, brevicolpate, small; polar area large (PAI=0.62). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Measurements</emphasis>
: pollen grains large, (73.59)81.71(93.64) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(76.00)81.23(86.72) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in equatorial view; exine thickness (2.85)3.19(3.48) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Exine</emphasis>
: marginated. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Ornamentation</emphasis>
: smooth surface with tectum perforate, ornated with spinules of (0.64)0.78(0.99) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
length 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(0.39)0.48(0.54) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diameter in base; perforations (0.05)0.11(0.19) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter (
